The paper focuses on link prediction and attribute inference in social networks, which falls under the categories of social networks (cs.SOC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of network structure and node attribute information also suggests the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper uses various algorithms and techniques, which could fall under the categories of data science (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
